  "title": "AI will create more jobs for humans, not replace them, Amazon founder Bezos says",
  "description": "The Amazon founder, who now has robotics and space travel companies, thinks AI will create a labour shortage.",
  "text": "AI will lead to more need for workers. Rather than make people redundant, Amazon founder Jeff. Bezos predicted during an appearance at a tech conference in Paris. Bezos pushed back against growing concerns that AI. Will replace large numbers of workers. Instead he argued that the tech will unlock new opportunities and. Increase demand for human labour. This is in contradiction to some other tech and.",
